Robdeltonie 2023-04-29 11:34 PM
Hopefully, this doesn't break any server rules. If it is, please let me know and I'll gladly remove this post. Anyway, I started dabbling into different AI voice-changing tools, specifically So-VITS-SVC. I did so with one goal in mind: To finally create a version of Owl City's Honey and the Bee that features Taylor Swift instead of Breanne Duren. I don't have anything against Breanne, but considering Adam was likely considering Taylor for the song but it not working out due to scheduling issues, I wanted to re-create what could have been using the powers of AI. Now, I'm nowhere near as good a singer as Taylor Swift, and my singing voice is extremely low that I didn't think it would work well with it. So, I used Emvoice to re-create dry stems of most of Breanne's parts. I then used the aforementioned AI tool to transform the audio from Emvoice into audio that sounds like Taylor, and this was the result. It turned out...okay. I think the main issue is the fact that I'm using a computer-generated voice synth with AI, making Taylor's voice sound robotic in parts. The best solution would be to find someone else (preferably with a range close to Taylor's) that can sing Breanne's parts and run that through the AI. And before anyone asks, "Why didn't you use something like Spleeter to run Breanne's actual performance through the AI?", I did think about it. But between the parts overlapping with Adam's, the vocal processing, and the harmonies, I didn't think I could get a good result that way. Is there anyone here that would be willing to help me with this project? I've included a demo version of what I wound up getting so you can see how it currently sounds. Thanks!

OOPS! Studio! 2023-04-30 4:17 AM
I live in Seattle!! You should absolutely visit someday. I think you'd like it :) Just don't get your hopes up too much because there's lot of graffiti and garbage scattered around, heh. But the architecture here is beautiful, and the Puget Sound is awesome. The Space Needle, the EMP Museum, the Pacific Science Center... All kinds of awesome architecture and art to look at. Oh and also tons of rain, haha
4:19 AM
Also the greater Seattle area and the entire Pacific Northwest as a whole are beautiful too. So much green - tons of evergreen trees, tons of grass, parks, etc. And the water in the Pacific ocean is a very deep navy blue, unlike the Atlantic which is more cyan blue (which is also very beautiful!) The deep green and deep blue together look so pretty. Also the roads in Washington state are great, aha. Always very clean and safe and w i d e (edited)
